					<hr />
					<div style="margin: 0 5ex;">I think the bigger problem, as others mentioned, is shadow interests buying/selling to create speculative bubbles and subsequent crashes. &nbsp;They could orchestrate these events at critical times (during a version release or media event) to discourage new users. &nbsp;Shadow interests will have enormous funds and won&#039;t be concerned with making a profit.<br /><br />Even if they could corner the market, it wouldn&#039;t do them any good. &nbsp;The same goes for buying and destroying.&nbsp; Both would cause massive deflation and an ever higher price.</div>
